Lion Point Capital, LP Buys Hewlett Packard Enterprise Co, XPO Logistics Inc, Marathon Petroleum Corp, Sells Ally Financial Inc, HRG Group Inc, Yahoo! IncMay 15, 2017 |  About: 
HPE  +0%
XPO  +0%
MPC  +0%
JKS  +0%
PENN  +0%
WAC  +0%
YHOO  +0%
HZNP  +0% 



Investment company Lion Point Capital, LP buys Hewlett Packard Enterprise Co, XPO Logistics Inc, Marathon Petroleum Corp, JinkoSolar Holding Co, Penn National Gaming Inc, Walter Investment Management Corp, sells Ally Financial Inc, HRG Group Inc, Yahoo! Inc, Horizon Pharma PLC during the 3-months ended 2017-03-31, according to the most recent filings of the investment company, Lion Point Capital, LP. As of 2017-03-31, Lion Point Capital, LP owns 27 stocks with a total value of $632 million.  These are the details of the buys and sells.New Purchases: HPE, XPO, MPC, JKS, PENN, WAC, Added Positions: AA, BANC, Reduced Positions: ALLY, HRG, ARNC, ARNCPRB, Sold Out: YHOO, HZNP, 
HPE 30-Year Financial DataThe intrinsic value of HPEPeter Lynch Chart of HPEFor the details of Lion Point Capital, LP's stock buys and sells, go to http://www.gurufocus.com/StockBuy.php?GuruName=Lion+Point+Capital%2C+LPThese are the top 5 holdings of Lion Point Capital, LPiShares Russell 2000 (IWM) - 871,500 shares, 18.97% of the total portfolio. Ally Financial Inc (ALLY) - 4,659,903 shares, 15% of the total portfolio.  Shares reduced by 26.2%Ally Financial Inc (ALLY) - 3,700,000 shares, 11.91% of the total portfolio. SPDR S&P Oil & Gas Explor & Product (XOP) - 1,787,500 shares, 10.6% of the total portfolio. Marvell Technology Group Ltd (MRVL) - 3,400,000 shares, 8.22% of the total portfolio. New Purchase: Hewlett Packard Enterprise Co (HPE)Lion Point Capital, LP initiated holdings in  Hewlett Packard Enterprise Co.  The purchase prices were between $16.64 and $18.61, with an estimated average price of $17.37.   The stock is now traded at around $18.99. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 3.06%. The holdings were 1,147,508 shares as of 2017-03-31. New Purchase: XPO Logistics Inc (XPO)Lion Point Capital, LP initiated holdings in  XPO Logistics Inc.  The purchase prices were between $42.71 and $52.54, with an estimated average price of $47.22.   The stock is now traded at around $54.44. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 2.96%. The holdings were 390,000 shares as of 2017-03-31. New Purchase: Marathon Petroleum Corp (MPC)Lion Point Capital, LP initiated holdings in  Marathon Petroleum Corp.  The purchase prices were between $47.71 and $52.93, with an estimated average price of $49.78.   The stock is now traded at around $52.99. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 2.16%. The holdings were 270,000 shares as of 2017-03-31. New Purchase: JinkoSolar Holding Co Ltd (JKS)Lion Point Capital, LP initiated holdings in  JinkoSolar Holding Co Ltd.  The purchase prices were between $14.08 and $17.95, with an estimated average price of $15.84.   The stock is now traded at around $17.45. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 1.71%. The holdings were 652,720 shares as of 2017-03-31. New Purchase: Penn National Gaming Inc (PENN)Lion Point Capital, LP initiated holdings in  Penn National Gaming Inc.  The purchase prices were between $13.06 and $18.5, with an estimated average price of $14.66.   The stock is now traded at around $18.99. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.29%. The holdings were 98,583 shares as of 2017-03-31. New Purchase: Walter Investment Management Corp (WAC)Lion Point Capital, LP initiated holdings in  Walter Investment Management Corp.  The purchase prices were between $0.7 and $5.05, with an estimated average price of $3.08.   The stock is now traded at around $1.64. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.15%. The holdings were 900,000 shares as of 2017-03-31. Sold Out: Yahoo! Inc (YHOO)Lion Point Capital, LP sold out the holdings in  Yahoo! Inc.  The sale prices were between $38.9 and $46.78, with an estimated average price of $44.65. Sold Out: Horizon Pharma PLC (HZNP)Lion Point Capital, LP sold out the holdings in  Horizon Pharma PLC.  The sale prices were between $14.37 and $18.09, with an estimated average price of $16.2. Here is the complete portfolio of Lion Point Capital, LP. Also check out:
1. Lion Point Capital, LP's Undervalued Stocks
2. Lion Point Capital, LP's Top Growth Companies, and
3. Lion Point Capital, LP's High Yield stocks
4. Stocks that Lion Point Capital, LP keeps buying







